<br>
I totally agree with this assessment, Val. <br>
<br>
I have been told by numerous lady players that they have been burned out (bad experiences) from playing the sexy female avatars (wood elves, etc), in some cases they got stalked by wackos.  <br>
<br>
So what they end up doing is they retreat to playing &quot;unattractive female&quot; avatars like a female bearded Dwarf or a female Iksar or a big lumbering scary Ogress.  Hardly anyone flirts with a bearded Dwarf lady or a female Iksar (which is often mistaken for a male).  I was told that when the lady player ends up playing these, they end up feeling more secure that they are NEVER judged by their looks or gender.... they are only judged by their actions and capabilities.  It's really sad that many female players feel they have to be pushed to these options.  But I totally understand the reasoning.  <br>
<br>
For the female players that actively choose to play the &quot;unattractive female&quot; avatars.... if they manage to stick with it, they have my greatest respect.  It's not easy playing a female Troll or a female Ogre or even a bearded Dwarf.... in many cases they will be shunned by many other players.  Many players won't even bother to stop to say hello to you.  But the people that play these characters have my respect, because if I see them reach the higher levels.... I know for a fact that they earned everything, and they survived the challenge.  Everything they accomplished is most likely due to their deeds and actions, rather than because some horny male Dark Elf twinked them for some sexual flirtations. <br>
<br>
oh wait.... Moandor is a male Dark Elf.... oops, ok I take that back!  /grin <br>
<br>
Best of all, the female &quot;ugly races&quot; are some of the best role players I have ever seen in EQ.  <br>
<br>
Likewise, the VAST VAST majority of male players are loathe to play something like a bearded Dwarf or a pink-pantied Iksar female.  Most immature guys will get their kicks from playing some busty half naked wood elf babe, because they know they will attract attention.  But these same guys will loathe to play a big scary Ogress or a bearded Dwarf woman or even a wrinkly looking little gnome female. <br>
<br>
Personally I think the gnome females are cuties.... but only because I've played a gnome in the past and Gnome Powah resonates with me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A> at: 1/15/02 4:54:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 4:55:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ye roleplay with ladies but not with me ?!?</span><hr size=1> I like the Iksar ladies myself. *grins* <br>
