<br>
I love to flirt in roleplay as long as it's not taken to an extreme or seriously by anyone. My character, I'm finding, is kinda silly and this fits in with her perfectly, though I only do it now with males that I'm comfortable with, I don't flirt with every guy that comes along. Unfortunately, I'm finding the harrassment to be more the norm than the original posters comment about men doing more roleplay with women. <br>
<br>
I have specific people I group with often now but we don't make a full group and we'll usually pick up a few extra people to round out our group. I'm usually the only female character in the group and without fail, one of the new guys that comes in will start talking to me in /tell, and within five minutes they'll be making the moves. Generally I handle it the way I handle it in RL, brush them off with a laugh, but trying not to hurt anyone's feelings. I've only had one incident that really ticked me off.<br>
<br>
I guess it's a fine line, and how the guy goes about it, it can be kind of funny in certain situations. Last night I was talking to a guy friend, we were facing each other, when I here &quot;Hail, Narie&quot; from behind me. I turn around and it's a nekkid Barbarian on a long CR, he asks if I would mind giving him a SoW, and of course I do, he then bows to me, and I bow to him, then I see my friend on the chat screen chuckling. I said &quot;Hey, I just gave you the full moon didn't I?&quot; and he replies with &quot;Yep, I was waiting for it&quot;, we both laugh and move on. <br>
<br>
/sigh Oh well, as one of my friends said the other day when we were discussing this, &quot;Nothing like running around killing monsters in a g-string&quot;. <p>Narie<br>
